The paper deals with communication complexity and lower bounds in the context of distribution testing, which are topics typically studied in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The specific problem of distribution testing falls under the umbrella of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of secure distribution testing, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR).
